Commit message: \this commit contains the reimplementation of the scoping. The complete scoping is removed from the ACG. Additionally some code from the ACG is transfered in a Helper that manges labels, scopes and variable creation in a stack. All checks from JSRVariableScopeCodeVisitor are transfered into the ClassCompletion verifier or the new VariableScopeVisitor. Additionally some checks for labels were added with the LabelVerifier. ACG was changed so a DeclarationExpression will no longer create a local variable and if a variable is a filed or protperty accessed from inside a closure ACG will no longer try to access that field directly. Instead the closure has to resolve these cases at runtime.

Commit message: \summary of post-PR changes: - revert back to nd4j 0.5.0 (for the time being, it is the most memory efficient release) - made ComputableGraphStructure serializable (not necessary -- just for better semantics) - added a method to ICG to "nullify" a cached value (used for freeing up memory) - removed the NEGLECT_ZERO_COPY_NUMBER_STATE back in calculating log copy ratio posteriors; inclusion of finite mapping error correction to copy ratios obviates this - added IntegerCopyNumberReferenceStateFactory; essentially, a bi-fuction that takes a target and sex genotypes and gives the reference copy number state - improved Nd4jIOUtils; we can now read/write tensors to tab-separated files - the reported log likelihood now includes are normalization factors and the contribution from the HMM chain - CoverageModelCopyRatioEmissionProbabilityCalculator takes into account mapping error in the laplace approximation as well (this still has to be replaced with the "proper" laplace approximation) - ARD for bias covariates; this affects many classes (mainly CoverageModelEMWorkspace and CoverageModelEMComputeBlock) - PCA initialization of bias covariates - removed unnecessary setters in CoverageModelEMParams; added a validation method - some code cleanup and refactoring in CoverageModelEMWorkspace and CoverageModelEMComputeBlock (mostly relating to posterior initialization) - new methods in CoverageModelEMWorkspaceMathUtils for calculating eigensystems, log det, etc - added methods to clear caches values from variable transition probability caches - we no longer collect fbResults to the master node as they are too large to fit in a single machine's memory with 3+ copy number states. Instead, HiddenMarkovModelSegmentProcessor directly gives viterbi results (calculations are done on worker nodes). - added a method to ForwardBackwardAlgorithm to calculate the log data likelihood excluding emission lines (only the chain); this is useful in reporting the correct log likelihood in variational Bayes problems after updating some posteriors that affect emission probability, though, still using the old copy ratio posteriors - improved concordance statistics report in CoverageModellerGermlineSparkToggleIntegrationTest - extra unit tests for Nd4j-related methods - updated unit test resources
Labels for what and how: Adding entirely new comment & under development: commented code

Commit message: \Several improvements in documentation of classes from the package org.cloudbus.cloudsim. The documentation of classes, methods and attributes were improved to make them clearer. Many times the documentation of attributes and parameters just repeated the name of the attribute itself. Some methods didn't have a clear explanation of their goals or lacked some important details that were included. Some ambiguous terms such as "machine", that can mean a "virtual" or a "physical machine", where accordingly changed by the specific term to avoid confusion. Some methods also had ambiguous meanings. Methods such as getUtilization of the UtilizationModel class return the utilization percentage of some resource. Other methods such as getUtilizationOfRam on HostDynamicWorkload class returns the absolute value of a resource usage (not percentage), what is not accordingly described in the documentation. These inconsistencies were corrected in the documentation.

Commit message: \Fixed bugs that caused references pushed on the marking stack to be visited twice. The problem originates from the way the mark bitmap is scanned. The mark word needs to be reread after every visit to a cell corresponding to a grey mark in order to catch grey mark that may have been set in that same word. Some of these marks may be before the current "finger", causing their reference to be pushed on the marking stack by the cell visitor, but visited immediately after by the mark bitmap scan. This happens because the scan of the mark bitmap word doesn't check if a grey bit is before the finger or not.

I still need to setup the modified htree constructor which accepts the prefixLength, depth(root), and depth(root.parent) and I still need to modify insert() to use that information.  The additional fields provided to the constructor are only used when the temporary htree is being used to rebuild a directory page (and the spanned child pages).  They provide sufficient information to index into the root of the temporary htree when its depth is LT address bits.  (The root directory page of a normal HTree is always at depth := addressBits. Cleaned up MetadataStore and MetadataRetrieve interface usage:     * Renamed OMEXMLMetadataStore to OMEXMLMetadata.     * Created MetadataTools utility class with conversion methods between       OMEXMLMetadata, OME-XML string, and other ("foreign") MetadataStore       and MetadataRetrieve object types.     * Migrated existing convertMetadata(MetadataRetrieve, MetadataStore)       method from FormatTools to MetadataTools.     * Also included useful reflection methods for working with OMEXMLMetadata       objects without depending on loci.formats.ome package at compile time.     * Reworked places that uses OMEXMLMetadata objects via reflection to use       new MetadataTools utility methods instead.     * Reworked OMETiffReader and OMETiffWriter to be more flexible about       their assigned MetadataStore and MetadataRetrieve objects, respectively;       using the MetadataTools convertMetadata functionality, even foreign       metadata object implementations are usable.   2. Eliminated a few catch-all exception handling blocks, but still some left.   3. Some miscellaneous cleanup and tweaks.   4. Given the scope of the changes, I probably broke something.      If anything stops working for you, please let me know.

Commit message: \Implemented Operations to simplify get indexes and find and modify (find & remove/replace/update).  As part of this work:   - Refactored write operations so that they no longer require a Command.  Command is being phased out in favour of containing the functionality in Operations classes.   - This meant changing classes further up the stack to deal only with Documents without wrapping them in a Command, simplifying the code in most places   - Created a DocumentHelper to make creation of things like command documents a lot simpler   - Greater test coverage for the areas affected by the new operations; also added tests to areas affected by refactoring   - Moved creation of Settings objects into MongoClient classes, a refactoring that makes creating tests for the operations a lot simpler   - Created CommandWithPayloadEncoder and CommandResultWithPayloadDecoder to allow correct use of custom encoders for find and replace/remove/update.  Find and Replace now works with custom types.   - Fixed Exceptions for command results that return a custom type   - Ignored a Find Bugs warning for all classes, since it was adding nothing and was ignored for all classes it was found in
Labels for what and how: Deleting obsolete comment & tool related: directive

Commit message: \Several improvements in documentation of classes from the package org.cloudbus.cloudsim. The documentation of classes, methods and attributes were improved to make them clearer. Many times the documentation of attributes and parameters just repeated the name of the attribute itself. Some methods didn't have a clear explanation of their goals or lacked some important details that were included. Some ambiguous terms such as "machine", that can mean a "virtual" or a "physical machine", where accordingly changed by the specific term to avoid confusion. Some methods also had ambiguous meanings. Methods such as getUtilization of the UtilizationModel class return the utilization percentage of some resource. Other methods such as getUtilizationOfRam on HostDynamicWorkload class returns the absolute value of a resource usage (not percentage), what is not accordingly described in the documentation. These inconsistencies were corrected in the documentation.
